+# Infra Discussion Review — task-260415-124500
+
+Date: 2026-04-15
+Scope: D3 — Smoke-test S280 Pipeline Hardening
+
+## Summary
+- Discussion-only task completed without application code changes.
+- The synced checkout at `5fc308ecaf42a8bcf2a90de53c19fd9f00d38fc3` does not contain `scripts/task-watcher-multi.py` or `cleanup_stale_git_locks`, so the recommendations below are based on the task's stated helper contract and the existing Infra bug notes.
+
+## Recommended Improvements
+1. Add a liveness check before deleting any "stale" Git lock.
+Why: `mtime > 60s` is not enough to prove abandonment on slow disks, during long rebases, or when antivirus/network latency delays a real Git operation. The safer pattern is "old plus no live owner" or at least "old twice across two checks."
+
+2. Expand lock coverage with a strict allowlist and better diagnostics.
+Why: the current helper contract only covers a few lock paths, so the pipeline can still fail on `packed-refs.lock`, `config.lock`, `shallow.lock`, or other ref locks while cleanup reports success. Structured logging of path, age, and delete/skip reason would also make Telegram alerts actionable.
+
+## Trade-offs
+- The liveness guard adds platform-specific logic or an extra retry cycle.
+- The broader sweep must stay allowlisted so the helper does not become too aggressive inside `.git`.
+
+## Deliverables
+- Position file mirror: `pipeline/chain-state/infra-260415-123810-8239-codex-position.md`
+- Round note: `pages/Infra/round1_2026-04-15_task-260415-124500.md`
+- Command log: `pages/Infra/commands_2026-04-15_task-260415-124500.log`
+
+## Environment Notes
+- Direct writes to `C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/pipeline/...` were blocked by the sandbox, so mirrored files were created under the repo-local `pipeline/` directory instead.
